NAME
orpgrda_adpt - ORPG RDA Adaptation DATA Support (RDA_ADPT) routines

SYNOPSIS

#include <orpg.h>

void* ORPGRDA_ADPT_read();
void* ORPGRDA_ADPT_get_data();


OVERVIEW
The functions are described separately below.

NAME
ORPGRDA_ADPT_read()

SYNOPSIS
#include <orpg.h>

void* ORPGRDA_ADPT_read()

DESCRIPTION
Sets up LB notification for ORDA adaptation data updates if not already 
registered.  Reads ORDA adaptation data from data store and returns a pointer
to the data structure.

RETURNS
On success, returns a (void*) pointer to a ORDA_adpt_data_t structure
or a NULL pointer on error.


NAME
ORPGRDA_ADPT_get_data()

SYNOPSIS
#include <orpg.h>

int ORPGRDA_ADPT_get_data()

DESCRIPTION
Will read the ORDA adaptation data from data store if data has been updated
since last read.  Otherwise just returns a pointer to the ORDA adaptation
data structure.  

RETURNS
On success, returns a (void*) pointer to a ORDA_adpt_data_t structure
or a NULL pointer on error.

NAME
ORPGRDA_ADPT_get_data_value()

SYNOPSIS
#include <orpg.h>

int ORPGRDA_ADPT_get_data_value( int item, void *value )

DESCRIPTION
Selected values used by ORPG are returned through "value". See orpgrda_adpt.h
for macro definitions of recognized items. 

RETURNS
On success, returns 0.  On error, returns -1.

